
FIND CROPPED REGIONS

util.py
<- image(s)
-> contiguous regions to crop

each region has:
1. image name
2. size
3. position

region name = <imagename>_<regionindex>

CREATE CROPPED IMAGES

use imagemagick to create a cropped image for each region

convert <imagename> -crop WxH+X+Y +repage <imagename>_<regionindex>

PACK CROPPED IMAGES

call ZeroSprites
<- region filenames
-> packed image and location data

CREATE ENGINE TEXTURE METADATA

1. list of images
	a. image name
	b. list of regions
		i. size
		ii. source position
		iii. destination position
2. list of animations
	a. fps
	b. list of frames
		i. list of regions
			* image name
			* region index
